.TH "ldm_validate_vmdb" 9 "ldm_validate_vmdb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ldm_validate_vmdb \- Read the VMDB and validate it
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" ldm_validate_vmdb
.BI "(struct parsed_partitions *state "  ","
.BI "unsigned long base "  ","
.BI "struct ldmdb *ldb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
Partition check state including device holding the LDM Database
.IP "base" 12
Offset, into \fIbdev\fP, of the database
.IP "ldb" 12
Cache of the database structures
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find the vmdb of the LDM Database stored on \fIbdev\fP and return the parsed
information in \fIldb\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
'true'   \fIldb\fP contains validated VBDB info
'false'  \fIldb\fP contents are undefined
